The paper deals with a wireless communication problem in a network with high-mobility users, which involves optimizing the allocation of pilot sequences. This problem is related to several sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on wireless communication and signal processing, we believe that cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.LG.
